			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>i agree with ramesh, as i read how listening devices like the ones found here on <a href="http://www.audiointercept.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.audiointercept.com</a> are used for audio surveillance only, while there may be body language involved that may not be visible to an audio surveillance recording. however, for law enforcement purposes, it may seem that what a person says is what it is, and that is a record of their speech.</p>
